<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1890-07-20T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1890-07-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="27" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d27">
                    <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Blaine</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Mizner</persName></hi>.</head>
                    <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1890-07-20"><hi rend="italic">July</hi> 20,
                            1890</date>.</dateline></opener>
                    <p>Mr. Blaine instructs Mr. Mizner promptly to demand of the Guatemalan
                        Government the instant surrender of the <hi rend="italic">Colima</hi>, with
                        all her cargo, that Government having no right whatever to detain her, as
                        she had been guilty of no offense against any treaty existing or against the
                        law of nations.</p>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>